Definition
-> Moves element relative to nearest positioned parent.
-> If no positioned parent, it uses the body.
-> Space is NOT reserved.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.parent {
 position: relative;
 height: 200px;
 border: 2px solid black;
}

.child {
 position: absolute;
 top: 20px;
 right: 20px;
 background: orange;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="parent">
 <div class="child">Absolute Box</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

📌 It removes element from normal flow.
